This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a machine learning algorithm for uncertainty prediction. It also involves the use of deep ensemble networks, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. 

The paper involves experiments related to classification and regression, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). 

Finally, the paper proposes a method for optimizing ensembles, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
